          <h2>Program Overview</h2>
          <p>Our ARTS in Prison -- Think Motion program delivers music, theater, and movement-based experiences that foster healing, self-expression, and growth. We believe that artistic expression is a fundamental human right and a powerful tool for transformation, even behind prison walls.</p>
          
          <p>The program provides a constructive outlet for personal growth, emotional processing, and skill development—demonstrating the profound impact of the arts on rehabilitation and successful community reintegration.</p>
          
          <h2>Program Components</h2>
          <h3>Think Motion Movement Workshop</h3>
          <p>A trauma-informed movement program that uses:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Expressive dance and embodied movement</li>
            <li>Yoga and mindfulness practices</li>
            <li>Theater games and improvisation</li>
            <li>Body awareness and emotional regulation</li>
            <li>Group choreography and collaboration</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Music & Songwriting</h3>
          <p>Participants learn to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Write, workshop, and perform original songs</li>
            <li>Play instruments and understand music theory</li>
            <li>Use music as a tool for storytelling and healing</li>
            <li>Build confidence through performance</li>
            <li>Process trauma and emotions through lyrics</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Visual Arts & Creative Writing</h3>
          <p>Artistic expression through:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Painting, drawing, and mixed media</li>
            <li>Poetry and creative writing workshops</li>
            <li>Exploration of various artistic techniques</li>
            <li>Building confidence and discipline</li>
            <li>Exhibition opportunities for completed work</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>Program Impact</h2>
          <h3>Healing & Self-Discovery</h3>
          <p>The arts provide a safe space for participants to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Process complex emotions and trauma</li>
            <li>Develop healthy coping mechanisms</li>
            <li>Build self-esteem and purpose</li>
            <li>Explore identity beyond incarceration</li>
            <li>Develop emotional resilience</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Skill Development</h3>
          <p>Participants gain valuable skills:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Creative problem-solving</li>
            <li>Communication and collaboration</li>
            <li>Project planning and execution</li>
            <li>Public performance and presentation</li>
            <li> constructive self-expression</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Community & Connection</h3>
          <p>The program creates:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Positive peer relationships</li>
            <li>Mentorship opportunities with teaching artists</li>
            <li>Connection to outside communities</li>
            <li>Supportive creative community inside prison</li>
            <li>Bridges to post-release arts programs</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2>Current Programs</h2>
          <p>Our Arts in Prison programming currently operates in collaboration with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Arizona Department of Corrections facilities</li>
            <li>Local teaching artists and arts organizations</li>
            <li>University arts education departments</li>
            <li>Community theater and music groups</li>
          </ul>
          
          <p><strong>We are actively seeking funding and partnerships to expand our reach to additional facilities and program areas.</strong></p>
